content: Today, we will analyse an interesting variant,
which was played in game Soosé®®v-Meritee,
The time limit was 50 minutes, and without preparation, it is difficult to play such variants.
How many of you know this 5th move?
I did not know this move either.
I spent quite some time to decide about 6th move.
dongfujia, you cannot play 6th move to g8 - there is a black stone
I was thinking of i8 first.
But then I thought, Ants would go g10 here
and I could not find a way.
Who can try white now, say me.
no clear advantage to either side
as white player, i would not want to get this position, anyway
so I wanted to find something better.
Finally I decided, this 6th move can be best.
But I was also confused same time.
so I was thinking, if 6-g8 is "best"
logic says - this 6th must be worse than g8
but i could not find any reason!!
Where must black go - left or right?
yes alicecooper, its quite possible that old theory was not perfect.
Today we will find out, hopefully
the one who is "Free", must find
if he cannot find, next one can say "me"
Now, 9th move is a question for us.
Where do you think is a good 9th?
i think g6, i8 and j9 are all interesting and must be studied - agree?
location of g6 stone in "positional" game is very poor
its only usefulness was - if black could directly win
but we proved, black cannot win
so g6 becomes a weak stone in positional battle
if you were a white, where would you go? left or right?
for "defense" purpose, L is better than R
then we can compare, which gives white more benefit
the rule of defense is: a good defense is not the "best defending move",
but the "sufficient defending move," which gives best value to self
in a quick look we can make sure,
both L and R are enough for defense.
j8 seems strong, but also gives black some material,
which can be used for weakening whites.
this move makes black weaker at once,
but also does not give white much power.
who wants to be black now

in real game, its rather crazy to play this way as black
u have not so much time
because we are testing just 1 branch there
white has hundreds of different attack ways
maybe in 1 branch, we cannot find white win,
Ikon, you make conclusion by outcome of 1 branch,
not by the position in gemeral
we spend too much time on meaningless gamble
in real game, one would never play like that
because so much to lose, and nothing to gain
white can always jump to defense if all wins fail
maybe we dont spend more time here
it is a positional game from this 12th move,
if white does not want attack straight
shall we also look at the 3rd possibility of 9th move?
Ants played this 9th against me in that game.
The next move was logical too - i played f8.
and now, black has to decide where to put.
if you were black, where would you put?
if black goes e7 or h10,
if black plays actively on right side, then black may simply waste all its resource very fast,
and give white even stronger base
now white is even stronger than before
So it seems, the wisest thing for black is to be passive now
no matter which one black chooses,
white would attack on opposite side.
following points, like f5 etc, can develop the space
too much gamble to play here as black
i would hate to be black here in real game
maybe in 1 min orc game is ok
but not in 2 hour games championships
because this looks most realistic for black.
In database, there have been two games by that.
i considered these two moves also,
but i did not like them much
So i risked and played more aggressively.
if to stop the diagonal pair,
white can increase power from i8
so its necessary to stop here
maybe 18 to right is even better
Ants used this 15th after long thinking.
at least we didnt find after game
but black can come to lower area with big power
white can come to lower area with big power
after the game, we analysed it for some time,
and we could not find any weakness of this 6th move.
And we examined most of variants together today,
with such 5th move, the 6-g9 is best.
i remember i lost a game in 1993 AT,
and he beat me with this 13th move.
but i lost many and forgot
maybe if you lose few, you will remember well
if you lose more, win few, you will remember wins
it seems that white three gives more power than standard
i hope that i can lose few
So, the game was very useful theoretical innovation.
It gave us a new solution.
But of course, it was thanks to your help today
because we together checked most of questions.
So, thank you for active study! We end now. See you next week!
losing in meaningful games are even better than getting a win in normal games :)
